text.tspan: Daily new estimated infections of COVID-19, United States
Mean estimates from epidemiological models of the true number of infections. Estimates differ because the models differ in data used and
assumptions made. Confirmed cases—which are infections that have been confirmed with a test—are shown for comparison.
Data source: ICL (2022); IHME (2022); YYG (2020); LSHTM (2020); WHO COVID-19 Dashboard
Note: This chart shows the latest available model estimates as of 31 March 2023. The LSHTM, YYG, and IHME models have stopped releasing updates. The
uncertainty range for each estimate — which can be large — is not shown here but can be found in the individual model charts.
